# Conditional Statements

# if- else

1) Check whether a number is greater or not
  Program:-
  num = int(input("Enter a number: "))
  if(num>2):
      print("greater than 2")
  else:
      print("less than 2")
  Output:-
  Enter a number: 5
  greater than 2

2) Traffic light colours 
    Program:-
    light="Green"
    if (light == "Red"):
        print("stop")
    elif (light == "Green"):
        print("Go")
    elif (light == "Yellow"):
        print("Look")
    else:
        print("light is broken")
    print("end of code")
    Output:-
    Go
    end of code

3) Voting
    Program:-
    age = int(input("Enter you age: "))
    if age > 18:
        print("You eligible to vote")
    else:
        print("you are not eligible to vote")
    Output:- 
    a) Enter you age: 8
       you are not eligible to vote
    b) Enter you age: 20
       You eligible to vote

4) Exam Results
    Program:-
    marks = int(input("Enter your marks: "))
    if marks >= 90:
        print("Grade A")
    elif marks >= 80 and marks < 90:
        print("Grade B")
    elif marks >= 70 and marks < 80:
        print("Grade C")
    elif marks > 70:
        print("Grade D")
    Output:-
    Enter your marks: 96
    Grade A
